<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,791,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,419,791,816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This subgenus differs from all other subgenera of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowe" authorityYear="1840" box="[1162,1307,792,816]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1162,1307,792,816]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cheilopogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in smaller number of vertebrae and in the absence of chin barbels and enlarged dorsal fin (&quot;Parexocoetus&quot; stage) in juveniles (this stage is also absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1843" box="[460,590,864,888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Ptenichthys">
<emphasis box="[460,590,864,888]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ptenichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). From the genus 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="sensu Parin" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[797,923,864,888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[797,923,864,888]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in an elongate lower jaw protruding in front of the upper jaw, and in the presence of sharp (often recurved) unicuspid jaw teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,791,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,935,960]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the subgenus reflects the characteristics of the 
<typeStatus box="[1020,1068,936,960]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
species—the absence of barbels in juveniles and the presence of strong teeth on the jaws (from the Greek words Aµoυστάκoς (amustacas)—having no barbels and Περιτρώγoν (peritrógon)—toothed creature.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,791,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,574,1044,1069]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Composition of the subgenus.</emphasis>
We include two species in the subgenus: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kotthaus)" authorityName="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Kotthaus" baseAuthorityYear="1969" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus" subGenus="Amustotrogon">
<emphasis box="[1100,1245,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cheilopogon</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1269,1427,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Amustotrogon</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,254,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">formosus</emphasis>
(Kotthaus)
</taxonomicName>
(with 3 subspecies) and 
<emphasis box="[658,691,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ch</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin, 2019" authorityName="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin" authorityYear="2019" box="[704,875,1080,1104]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marisrubri" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Amustotrogon">
(
<emphasis box="[714,731,1080,1103]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[754,875,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">marisrubri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[883,972,1079,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[883,972,1079,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
